02:55.008 --> 02:58.843
- She canceled?
- New assistant. All his fault.

02:58.929 --> 03:01.296
- How's next week?
- How about now?

03:02.182 --> 03:06.017
Rest assured, she's making time
for an interview with <i>Vogue.</i>

03:06.103 --> 03:08.846
First African-American
woman National Security Advisor.

03:09.022 --> 03:12.186
Yeah, it's a big deal. I get it.

03:12.359 --> 03:14.726
Get me Condoleezza Rice
on the phone right now, please.

03:15.946 --> 03:17.903
Annie Leibovitz will photograph.

03:18.365 --> 03:19.901
They called me for a quote.

03:20.033 --> 03:22.116
She doesn't get it. None of them do.

03:22.285 --> 03:24.868
Every new administration
must be brought up to speed

03:24.955 --> 03:27.038
on the current
national security climate.

03:27.165 --> 03:29.703
Eight years ago, with Bush Sr.,
it was all about the Russians.

03:29.793 --> 03:31.329
Right? So, now, it is again.

03:31.878 --> 03:34.621
Anything Clinton cared about
must have been bullshit.

03:34.715 --> 03:36.752
He went north? We'll go south.

03:36.842 --> 03:39.004
Meanwhile, the threat matrix
is through the roof.

03:39.094 --> 03:40.585
That's what I'm trying to tell her.

03:40.679 --> 03:42.295
Try harder.

03:42.389 --> 03:45.678
Get their attention.
Scare the shit out of 'em.

03:46.393 --> 03:47.383
Yeah.

03:55.986 --> 03:57.193
She will call me back.

03:58.989 --> 04:02.073
Sure. She's a busy lady.

04:02.242 --> 04:04.825
<i>And if you are justjoining us,
we have breaking news to tell you</i>

04:04.911 --> 04:08.825
<i>about a terrorist convicted
of 213 counts of murder</i>

04:08.915 --> 04:12.283
<i>in the 1998 bombing
of the American embassy in Kenya,</i>

04:12.461 --> 04:17.297
<i>will be sentenced to life in prison
without the possibility of parole.</i>

04:17.382 --> 04:20.216
Yes! Yes! Chesney!

04:20.385 --> 04:22.798
Chesney! Chesney! Chesney!

04:27.726 --> 04:31.970
Justice was served.
So much time, so much effort. A hero.

04:32.105 --> 04:33.937
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

04:35.859 --> 04:40.274
The American justice system worked.
You should all sleep very well tonight.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.237
This is all you. Are you proud?

04:42.324 --> 04:44.031
I couldn't have done it
without Kathy and Floyd.

04:44.576 --> 04:45.737
Oh.

04:45.827 --> 04:47.489
Go back to work!

04:48.413 --> 04:50.905
Now, they're gonna want to make
a martyr out of him.

04:50.999 --> 04:52.661
Listen, I put in a request.

04:52.751 --> 04:55.835
You're gonna do a
language school intensive, learn Arabic.

04:56.505 --> 04:57.712
I don't want to do that.

04:57.798 --> 05:01.166
You learned Romanian, didn't you?
It can't be as hard as Romanian.

05:01.551 --> 05:04.669
It's too late for me. I'm coming up
on retirement, same as you.

05:04.888 --> 05:08.052
So what? They're not gonna
push you out the door. They need you.

05:09.768 --> 05:12.385
When it comes, I'll be ready to go.

05:17.192 --> 05:20.776
I know. I know. Don't worry.

05:21.947 --> 05:24.360
It's a good idea. Ah.

05:29.079 --> 05:30.069
No, of course.

05:33.166 --> 05:35.749
He's here right now. I'll ask him.

05:35.836 --> 05:38.544
Okay, then. Bye-bye.

06:06.324 --> 06:09.237
But, Dad,
you can't have another one until midday.

06:09.619 --> 06:12.487
I know it hurts.

06:15.041 --> 06:18.910
Yes, okay. I promise I'll call
the doctor. I'll see you later.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.377
- Okay.
- Thank you.

06:20.505 --> 06:23.543
<i>The aircraft is controlled
from the cockpit, or flight deck.</i>

06:23.633 --> 06:26.626
<i>The pilot sits in the left seat,
and the copilot sits to the right,</i>

06:26.720 --> 06:28.632
<i>with the control column
located in the center.</i>

06:29.347 --> 06:30.963
<i>In front of them
is the instrument panel,</i>

06:31.057 --> 06:32.389
<i>containing the flight controls</i>

06:32.475 --> 06:34.512
<i>enabling a smooth and safe flight.</i>

06:34.603 --> 06:37.220
<i>The pilot and copilot
examine the aircraft logs</i>

06:37.314 --> 06:38.896
<i>and verify that all the controls
are in the proper position...</i>

06:49.367 --> 06:52.860
<i>Even as a kid, I knew
most Americans really didn't get it.</i>

06:53.079 --> 06:57.699
<i>They didn't understand
how the world worked. What was fake,</i>

06:57.876 --> 07:02.246
<i>and what was a bullshit distraction
from the way things really were,</i>

07:02.380 --> 07:05.339
<i>corrupt, evil.</i>

07:05.592 --> 07:07.675
<i>I knew there were
good guys and bad guys,</i>

07:08.887 --> 07:11.595
<i>and I wanted to be one of the good guys.</i>

07:12.015 --> 07:16.259
But at the same time,
I appreciate I can be overzealous.

07:16.394 --> 07:18.010
I also appreciate that sometimes,

07:18.104 --> 07:21.643
the right thing to do,
is to turn the other cheek.

07:21.733 --> 07:24.100
You pulled me out of Yemen,
in the middle of an investigation.

07:24.194 --> 07:26.311
I'm not gonna ask why,
or what that's about.

07:26.488 --> 07:29.652
I'm just here to tell you
that the investigation was going well.

07:29.741 --> 07:33.451
I picked the right case agent, too.
Soufan's young, but he's whip-smart.

07:33.536 --> 07:37.246
Presumably, the Yemenis trust him.
He's from around there, correct?

07:37.415 --> 07:39.077
He was born in Lebanon.
They don't trust him

07:39.167 --> 07:42.080
any more than they trust any American.
Less, maybe.

07:42.170 --> 07:45.004
But in spite of this,
he was the right man for the job.

07:45.674 --> 07:46.664
If you say so.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.250
I made personal connections
with some of the key players,

07:49.344 --> 07:52.052
got some leads, but they know more.

07:52.138 --> 07:55.552
Like to get back over there before
they forget how much they like me.

07:55.684 --> 07:56.765
So, when am I going back?

07:58.436 --> 07:59.472
You're not.

07:59.854 --> 08:01.766
You've been denied re-entry into Yemen.

08:04.859 --> 08:07.943
- Who did that?
- Ambassador Bodine.

08:08.029 --> 08:11.773
Apparently, you didn't make personal
connections with all the key players.

08:11.950 --> 08:13.486
Did she say why?

08:13.743 --> 08:17.487
She said a lot of things,
but reading between the lines,

08:17.622 --> 08:20.239
I'd say she thought
you were kind of an asshole.

08:35.472 --> 08:37.385
Khallad rented the house
the bombers stayed in.

08:37.517 --> 08:39.759
We have to assume he was running
the operation on the ground.

08:39.852 --> 08:42.470
And we also have to acknowledge
that's an assumption.

08:42.605 --> 08:44.015
So, what do we know for sure?

08:44.190 --> 08:45.351
One leg.

08:45.442 --> 08:47.525
Fantastically
identifiable characteristic.

08:47.861 --> 08:51.354
He traveled from Malaysia to Bangkok
to meet Quso.

08:51.448 --> 08:54.907
Quso told you he gave him 36 grand.
Said it was for a new leg.

08:54.993 --> 08:56.234
Which I do not believe.

08:56.327 --> 08:58.364
And I'm taking
a second run at Quso later.

08:58.580 --> 08:59.866
Good deal.

09:00.123 --> 09:02.740
Have you talked
to your people at Langley?

09:02.834 --> 09:04.166
I told them what we're looking for.

09:04.836 --> 09:06.953
Yeah, I also told them
what we're looking for,

09:07.130 --> 09:10.089
but did you get an answer?
'Cause I didn't.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.388
He read in his <i>Lonely Planet Yemen</i>

09:18.475 --> 09:21.343
that the best food here
was the street food.

09:21.436 --> 09:22.426
So white.

09:24.731 --> 09:27.474
You asked them
for any information about Khallad,

09:27.567 --> 09:30.651
or anything on the Malaysia meeting,
the take from the Hada phone?

09:31.154 --> 09:32.736
Yup.

09:33.531 --> 09:38.276
And you told them we can't move forward
until they quit stonewalling?

09:38.828 --> 09:41.912
I didn't put it like that exactly,
but, yeah, basically.

09:42.624 --> 09:43.614
And?

09:44.751 --> 09:47.585
So, yeah, as you predicted,

09:47.670 --> 09:50.538
absolutely, there were phone calls
made from Quso's hotel room in Bangkok,

09:50.632 --> 09:52.043
to the Hada phone in Yemen,

09:52.133 --> 09:53.920
and from there
to a payphone in Malaysia.

09:55.804 --> 09:58.296
Wait, Chihoyne,
you kind of buried the lede.

09:58.723 --> 10:01.215
We're getting those transcripts?

10:01.309 --> 10:03.141
No.

10:03.228 --> 10:06.346
I mean, they're not passing anything on.
They're saying it's not pertinent.

10:06.815 --> 10:08.226
"Not pertinent"?

10:08.316 --> 10:09.932
What the fuck does that mean?

10:10.026 --> 10:11.938
If they've got something,
it's pertinent.

10:12.362 --> 10:15.321
- I don't know, man.
- What do you mean, you don't know?

10:15.406 --> 10:18.240
Why am I going through you
if you can't get any fucking answers?

10:19.160 --> 10:22.653
- Fucking bureaucrat.
- Why don't you take it down a notch?

10:23.039 --> 10:25.622
A bunch of Americans
got blown out of the water

10:25.708 --> 10:28.746
and shipped home in pieces,
but let's take it down a notch

10:28.878 --> 10:32.087
because the Agency is the Agency,
and what are you gonna do?

10:32.215 --> 10:33.672
Look, Ali... Ali, just...

10:33.758 --> 10:35.920
Aw, come on,
let's take it down a notch, Floyd.

11:09.502 --> 11:11.368
They all get their period
at the same time, or something?

11:16.593 --> 11:19.336
Yes, I saw Agent Soufan's cable.

11:19.679 --> 11:21.386
We were wondering if you'd like us

11:21.472 --> 11:24.055
to pull the relevant intel,
draft a response.

11:24.726 --> 11:27.184
If Leonard Bliss
wants a response drafted

11:27.270 --> 11:28.806
and you are required in that effort,

11:28.897 --> 11:30.854
then you will be alerted at that time.

11:31.357 --> 11:33.644
In the meantime,
should we let Agent Soufan know...

11:33.735 --> 11:35.943
In the meantime, you will continue
with what you were doing

11:36.029 --> 11:37.565
before he interrupted.

11:38.156 --> 11:40.990
We get hundreds of cables a day,

11:41.075 --> 11:45.410
and we do not dash off responses
like flighty coeds.

11:45.496 --> 11:47.738
I should get back to work.

11:49.959 --> 11:51.245
I don't want to dash anything off,

11:51.336 --> 11:53.578
but obviously,
his request is time-sensitive.

12:02.430 --> 12:05.047
The Bureau and the CIA were established

12:05.141 --> 12:09.385
as two distinct and separate
organizations for security reasons.

12:10.146 --> 12:11.557
We don't always have the same goals,

12:11.648 --> 12:14.766
and sometimes,
our goals conflict with each other.

12:14.943 --> 12:16.809
It is my belief and the belief
of my colleagues that...

12:16.945 --> 12:20.188
Schmidt? He doesn't work here anymore.

12:21.282 --> 12:23.114
...that there is no reason

12:23.201 --> 12:25.318
on God's green Earth
to jeopardize our own missions

12:25.411 --> 12:27.403
by solving the Bureau's crimes for them.

12:35.880 --> 12:38.623
How about this?

12:38.716 --> 12:43.006
Let's find out why
I-49 wants this information.

12:43.388 --> 12:46.756
Let's find out what they know already,
and we'll go from there.

12:48.017 --> 12:49.508
Sound good?

13:36.316 --> 13:37.352
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

13:37.483 --> 13:41.853
- Can I have one more hour, please?
- Uh, sure. It's not booked till 5:00.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.274
Thank you.

14:16.939 --> 14:18.521
I'll be right there.

14:24.280 --> 14:26.488
Hi, Toni-Ann.

14:26.657 --> 14:28.489
Listen, tomorrow,

14:28.618 --> 14:32.828
I want you to take these photographs
to your G-men buddies over at I-49

14:32.914 --> 14:35.281
and see if they recognize anyone.

14:37.502 --> 14:39.664
Well, I recognize al-Mihdhar.

14:40.421 --> 14:41.912
But will they?

14:42.006 --> 14:45.090
It's important that
we understand what they know.

14:45.301 --> 14:47.668
That way,
we can assess what information is,

14:47.929 --> 14:50.296
or isn't pertinent to their inquiries.

14:51.557 --> 14:53.014
And if they know nothing?

14:53.684 --> 14:55.425
Then come and tell me that.

16:13.055 --> 16:14.045
Hmm?

16:45.671 --> 16:49.665
- They gave you a day pass, huh?
- Can't wait for parole.

16:49.967 --> 16:51.048
I bet.

16:51.177 --> 16:54.045
You recognize
any of these goobers?

16:54.138 --> 16:55.470
Nope. Who are they?

16:56.140 --> 16:57.381
You don't recognize them?

16:57.558 --> 16:58.890
Should I? Who are they?

17:00.770 --> 17:03.604
This is Khalid al-Mihdhar.

17:05.942 --> 17:08.355
What the fuck is this,
"Quid pro quo, Clarice"?

17:08.444 --> 17:10.151
Who are the others?

17:11.571 --> 17:13.733
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

17:14.157 --> 17:16.400
No, they just want me
to see if you guys know.

17:16.536 --> 17:18.117
Wait a minute. Wait a minute.
But they know, right?

17:18.204 --> 17:19.740
These are their photographs.

17:19.872 --> 17:21.157
Yeah, I assume.

17:21.415 --> 17:24.954
- You assume? You didn't fucking ask?
- It doesn't work like that.

17:25.086 --> 17:26.417
- What the fuck, Toni-Ann?
- All right, all right.

17:26.503 --> 17:28.211
So, this is al-Mihdhar.
What else do you got?

17:28.297 --> 17:29.378
You got a birth date?

17:31.008 --> 17:32.624
- No.
- You got a passport number?

17:32.718 --> 17:34.459
- No.
- These are fucking useless.

17:34.595 --> 17:36.803
Okay. So, thanks for the help.

17:36.889 --> 17:39.256
You come in here.
You show us these photographs.

17:39.350 --> 17:41.216
- You won't say why.
- I don't know why!

17:41.310 --> 17:43.427
They keep this shit up,
more people are gonna get killed.

17:43.563 --> 17:45.020
- It's fuckin' pathetic.
- What the fuck is this?

17:45.106 --> 17:46.222
Got any other
fucking photographs?

17:46.315 --> 17:47.726
Whose side are you on?

17:47.858 --> 17:51.351
The fucking Agency
is turning our own people against us.

17:51.445 --> 17:54.028
You got a complaint? Write it up,
you put it through the proper channels.

17:54.365 --> 17:57.574
Okay, yeah.
I'll go out and buy myself a stamp.

17:57.702 --> 17:58.818
How about you drop the attitude?

17:58.953 --> 18:01.036
How about you show some loyalty
to your men?

18:02.164 --> 18:04.156
Where the fuck is John?
He should've been here today.

18:04.292 --> 18:05.954
He got called to D.C.

18:06.961 --> 18:08.042
How convenient.

18:10.006 --> 18:11.087
I bet he did.

18:11.257 --> 18:15.217
Hey, Bob. Forget John!
I'm your boss!

19:13.069 --> 19:14.059
Exactly.

19:50.231 --> 19:51.221
I don't know.

20:03.202 --> 20:06.070
If Mr. American Ali
doesn't want to talk anymore,

20:06.914 --> 20:08.701
let us end this conversation.

20:11.252 --> 20:12.663
Great.

20:13.838 --> 20:14.874
Take him away.

20:16.882 --> 20:18.874
He never even met bin Laden.

20:44.493 --> 20:48.237
When you showed me the list of suspects
held here, in Yemen,

20:48.330 --> 20:51.164
Abu Jandal was on that list, correct?

20:52.626 --> 20:53.867
How can I remember?

20:54.503 --> 20:58.338
I remember. Get him.

20:58.507 --> 20:59.497
Now.

20:59.717 --> 21:02.710
Unfortunately, that won't be possible.

21:04.472 --> 21:06.805
You want me to go to Qamish again?

21:06.891 --> 21:08.257
Embarrass you again?

21:11.896 --> 21:17.062
Go to who you like.
No one will let you speak to Abu Jandal.

21:38.255 --> 21:42.374
Are you giving her a ride?
Did her car break down?

21:49.350 --> 21:50.932
Amy approached me with some concerns

21:51.018 --> 21:53.476
regarding Mr. Ali Soufan's
recent correspondence

21:53.646 --> 21:58.858
and your instructions as to response,
or lack thereof.

21:59.610 --> 22:00.976
She approached you?

22:02.488 --> 22:04.605
She was concerned
you wouldn't take her seriously,

22:05.032 --> 22:06.989
whereas, I think
I've developed a reputation

22:07.117 --> 22:10.781
among some of the analysts
as having a somewhat avuncular energy.

22:11.956 --> 22:12.946
Oh, have you?

22:13.123 --> 22:15.911
She raises some good questions.
I assured her you'd be reasonable.

22:18.379 --> 22:21.213
I appreciate that the Bureau
and the Agency play different roles,

22:21.549 --> 22:23.461
but at the same time,
international terrorism

22:23.551 --> 22:25.213
may call for some adjustment

22:25.302 --> 22:27.919
in terms of how we deal
with intelligence issues.

22:28.347 --> 22:32.512
- I think that's very interesting.
- The FBI has an intelligence branch.

22:33.394 --> 22:37.138
But it's hard for me to see a downside.
Am I missing something?

22:37.231 --> 22:38.767
If we tell the FBI everything,

22:38.858 --> 22:41.020
they will run around the world
arresting minor players,

22:41.277 --> 22:45.487
often minor players from Saudi Arabia.
There will be headlines.

22:45.573 --> 22:48.111
Mr. and Mrs. Smith
from Shitsburgh, Pittsburgh,

22:48.200 --> 22:50.658
will be outraged
by America's special relationship

22:50.744 --> 22:52.155
with the Saudi royal family.

22:52.246 --> 22:56.536
After all, the Saudis harbor terrorists,
or so the FBI says.

22:56.625 --> 23:00.869
And the fundamentalists in Saudi Arabia
will be equally angry

23:00.963 --> 23:03.797
because clearly,
the Americans seek a war on Islam.

23:03.966 --> 23:06.299
Royal heads will roll.

23:06.385 --> 23:08.172
Fundamentalists will overrun the Palace,

23:08.262 --> 23:10.049
and their brethren
throughout the Middle East

23:10.139 --> 23:11.755
and beyond will be emboldened.

23:11.849 --> 23:14.387
Civil wars every which way.

23:14.476 --> 23:18.846
Iran, Iraq, Syria, Egypt, Pakistan.

23:19.815 --> 23:23.149
And as the blood dries
and fanatics rule the East,

23:23.694 --> 23:26.437
Mr. and Mrs. Smith
will be chowing down on their cereal,

