not yet understanding
that a seismic shift

23:30.034 --> 23:31.775
just took place
in the political structure

23:31.869 --> 23:34.532
of the Earth and they are fucked.

23:36.874 --> 23:38.831
Our job is very simple.

23:39.376 --> 23:41.584
Saudi Arabia must never go down.

23:41.670 --> 23:45.334
We have a delicate but very

23:45.424 --> 23:47.290
special relationship.

23:50.846 --> 23:53.088
Oh. Look at that.

23:53.557 --> 23:56.095
I'm low on gas.

23:56.185 --> 24:00.680
I see. I'm sorry.
Thank you for your time.

24:01.231 --> 24:03.689
You're tired. Take a sick day tomorrow.

24:05.277 --> 24:08.270
Actually, take the week.

24:21.001 --> 24:23.869
How often should a married couple
be making love?

24:35.766 --> 24:39.305
Radicalism prospers
in the gap between rising expectations

24:39.395 --> 24:41.011
and declining opportunities,

24:41.438 --> 24:44.727
especially where
the population is largely impoverished,

24:44.817 --> 24:46.353
where the art is impoverished,

24:46.443 --> 24:49.652
and where the men
are largely separated from the women.

24:50.447 --> 24:54.691
That is why we believe we are seeing
an abundance of it in the Middle East,

24:54.952 --> 24:59.367
as well as North Africa, Central Asia,
Pakistan, Afghanistan.

24:59.498 --> 25:03.412
The origins of Islamic fundamentalism,
we can save for another day.

25:03.544 --> 25:05.957
- But it's impossible to understand...
- Richard.

25:06.880 --> 25:07.870
Question?

25:08.298 --> 25:12.042
I have a lot of work to do.
The President has a lot of work to do.

25:12.136 --> 25:15.254
So, what I need from you today,
is the short version.

25:17.182 --> 25:18.673
How are you going
to advise the president

25:18.767 --> 25:20.508
if you just skim the CliffsNotes?

25:20.602 --> 25:23.891
I'd like to do a second degree.
I really would. I like to study.

25:23.981 --> 25:26.473
But I don't have time.
I have another meeting in a half hour.

25:27.234 --> 25:29.317
I told Reed
you should clear the morning.

25:29.403 --> 25:31.986
And I told Reed
you do not dictate my schedule.

25:32.072 --> 25:34.439
Reed? Turn the lights back on.

25:34.575 --> 25:38.159
Please do not blow off the research.
You need to understand this.

25:38.245 --> 25:41.079
We're talking about
the current greatest threat

25:41.206 --> 25:44.074
- to national security...
- Then let's keep this very simple.

25:44.168 --> 25:45.158
Who are they?

25:47.171 --> 25:49.834
Who's who? Who's al-Qaeda?

25:50.007 --> 25:51.498
- Right.
- That's precisely

25:51.633 --> 25:53.340
what I'm trying to explain to you.

25:55.137 --> 25:57.880
You reported directly
to President Clinton, did you not?

25:58.766 --> 26:00.849
I did. And President Clinton...

26:00.934 --> 26:04.427
You won't be needed
to report directly to President Bush.

26:04.563 --> 26:08.398
Take the deep dives. That's your job.
But when you put something in writing,

26:08.650 --> 26:12.064
if you want it to get to the President,
keep it pithy.

26:15.491 --> 26:17.608
- "Pithy"?
- Well, on point.

26:17.701 --> 26:20.364
Like I said, everyone's very busy.

26:25.626 --> 26:27.993
Abu Jandal has nothing
to do with the <i>Cole</i> bombing.

26:36.470 --> 26:37.927
Speak in English, please.

26:38.013 --> 26:40.221
- I like to practice.
- Fine.

26:40.891 --> 26:43.008
Let's speak in English.

26:43.102 --> 26:45.014
Your English is excellent, by the way.

26:46.939 --> 26:48.726
Flattery.

26:48.899 --> 26:51.983
You think flattery
will get you Abu Jandal?

26:52.111 --> 26:53.101
It will not.

26:53.654 --> 26:55.145
Why can't I speak to him?

26:56.240 --> 26:58.197
Because there is no need.

27:00.536 --> 27:01.652
Ah.

27:01.745 --> 27:04.032
You've spent your life among soldiers,

27:06.041 --> 27:09.330
protecting them,
risking your life for them.

27:10.254 --> 27:14.749
The men on the <i>Cole</i> were soldiers,
young soldiers.

27:14.842 --> 27:16.128
Won't you help them?

27:17.386 --> 27:21.471
First flattery, now, guilt.

27:21.890 --> 27:26.009
I'm surprised you didn't bring me
more of Brother John's cigars.

27:29.523 --> 27:34.143
Brother John says,
"Let Brother Ali talk to Abu Jandal."

27:40.534 --> 27:42.947
I'm sad to not do you this favor.

27:44.454 --> 27:45.661
You don't seem sad.

27:47.291 --> 27:50.034
My guess is, you are happy.

27:50.169 --> 27:52.126
You are happy because by denying me,

27:52.212 --> 27:54.795
you're making
the Yemeni government happy.

27:56.216 --> 27:57.707
And they'll reward you.

27:59.428 --> 28:01.215
What are you gonna get?

28:01.513 --> 28:05.427
Another medal? Bigger house?

28:10.564 --> 28:12.305
Tell me something.

28:12.399 --> 28:13.640
Did you commit to memory

28:13.734 --> 28:15.851
all of the prisoners
held in Yemeni jails?

28:16.111 --> 28:19.946
That name's
particularly easy to remember.

28:21.325 --> 28:23.817
It means "father of death."

29:09.915 --> 29:12.623
Ooh, gorgeous, Arnold.

29:12.709 --> 29:14.325
That looks excellent.

29:14.628 --> 29:15.744
Why a giraffe?

29:15.837 --> 29:16.918
Mmm.

29:17.798 --> 29:19.710
Well, I know why giraffes make me happy.

29:24.554 --> 29:27.843
- Um, I have to take this.
- Okay.

29:29.810 --> 29:30.891
Hello?

29:31.228 --> 29:33.311
It's me. How are you?

29:33.480 --> 29:37.850
- What's wrong? What happened?
<i>- Nothing's happened.</i>

29:37.943 --> 29:39.104
But we said you'd only call me

29:39.194 --> 29:40.810
when I'm at work
if there's an emergency.

29:41.238 --> 29:43.605
<i>That's why I leave the phone on.
That's why I bought the phone.</i>

29:43.740 --> 29:46.073
I know. There's no emergency. I...

29:48.078 --> 29:52.743
I mean, I just got a break, and I'm...
Sorry. I'll go.

29:52.916 --> 29:54.782
No, no, no. I just...

29:56.169 --> 29:58.456
How are you? Is everything okay?

29:58.755 --> 30:01.589
Totally fine. How are you?

30:02.801 --> 30:07.171
<i>What are you doing right now?
How are the kids?</i>

30:07.264 --> 30:09.256
They're... They're great.

30:09.349 --> 30:12.592
We're painting pictures
of what happiness looks like right now.

30:13.228 --> 30:14.969
I assume you painted me.

30:19.735 --> 30:20.725
How's Yemen?

30:21.695 --> 30:22.685
<i>Right.</i>

30:23.196 --> 30:24.812
You still won't say
that's where you are.

30:25.240 --> 30:26.776
Can't say.

30:27.367 --> 30:29.905
You can't say.

30:31.496 --> 30:33.203
Are you close to catching anybody?

30:34.291 --> 30:37.910
Hey, you know what?
I can't fucking talk about that.

30:38.003 --> 30:39.335
Why would you even ask me that?

30:39.463 --> 30:41.705
- I'm sorry. I just...
- Hey, just go teach, okay?

30:42.132 --> 30:44.966
<i>I shouldn't have called.
You didn't even want me to call.</i>

30:45.052 --> 30:47.044
No, you're right. I didn't. I'm working.

30:47.387 --> 30:51.097
Yeah, me, too.
And I'm doing my fucking best, okay?

30:54.728 --> 30:56.060
Hello?

30:56.646 --> 30:57.762
She hang up on you?

30:59.733 --> 31:01.565
That's crazy.

31:01.902 --> 31:03.518
You were being so charming.

31:06.990 --> 31:09.607
Come on, man. Let's go back inside.

31:16.666 --> 31:20.159
I mean, what am I supposed to do?
Turn the other cheek?

31:20.921 --> 31:23.709
Be a lamb? You know
what that means. Be passive?

31:23.799 --> 31:28.214
No. Jesus never asks us to be passive.

31:28.345 --> 31:30.428
I gotta figure something out.
They're coming for me.

31:30.514 --> 31:32.506
I don't know why, but they are.

31:33.392 --> 31:35.475
- And how...
- You know what? I do know why.

31:35.560 --> 31:37.051
Office politics.

31:37.312 --> 31:39.554
I was never one
for office politics, you know?

31:39.648 --> 31:41.059
I always told people,
"You can either love me

31:41.149 --> 31:43.061
"or hate me, but your life
will be easier if you love me."

31:45.278 --> 31:48.191
I guess that isn't working anymore.

31:49.324 --> 31:51.156
So, fine, I, you know...

31:52.744 --> 31:57.409
I gotta deal with it,
kiss up to these guys,

31:57.541 --> 31:59.032
treat them like a jealous girlfriend,

31:59.126 --> 32:02.164
buy them flowers, talk pretty,
you know?

32:02.254 --> 32:05.622
Crazy waste of time
when lives are on the line.

32:07.259 --> 32:09.592
Well, how are the things
in your personal life?

32:10.011 --> 32:14.972
Professional troubles never seem so bad
if the home is a safe harbor.

32:16.476 --> 32:17.762
Listen.

32:19.980 --> 32:23.098
The world's in chaos. Okay?

32:26.903 --> 32:29.611
Men screw everything up.

32:32.742 --> 32:36.486
I know I'm part of that.
We both know I'm part of that.

32:40.292 --> 32:43.251
But I'm trying to put things right.

32:44.921 --> 32:47.914
Do you want to make a confession?

32:55.307 --> 32:59.517
Oh, God! Oh, God, Johnny.

32:59.728 --> 33:02.220
Oh, Johnny. Oh, Johnny.

33:02.355 --> 33:06.725
Oh, God! Johnny! Oh, I love you!
I love you, Johnny.

33:06.943 --> 33:11.278
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

33:15.952 --> 33:17.193
You can't blow these out.

33:17.454 --> 33:19.696
- Careful, honey.
- Make a wish, girls.

33:35.347 --> 33:36.337
John?

33:39.476 --> 33:40.466
Honey?

33:42.354 --> 33:44.141
I'm fine.

33:45.649 --> 33:47.481
Everything's fine.

33:53.782 --> 33:55.239
Yo, we leave at 6:00, Ali.

33:55.992 --> 33:57.153
Yeah, Mommy, I know.

33:57.244 --> 34:00.612
He's got to get his girl something nice.
She's pissed at him.

34:01.331 --> 34:05.325
My dad was a cop.
Worked a ton of overtime,

34:05.460 --> 34:08.293
and my mom was always sad, mad,

34:08.797 --> 34:11.915
long-suffering
'cause he was never home, and so,

34:12.007 --> 34:14.375
he got sad and mad
and never wanted to be home.

34:15.094 --> 34:19.179
And what teenage Floyd figured out
was that in this business,

34:19.266 --> 34:21.632
you gotta date someone
in the same line of work.

34:22.351 --> 34:23.592
Civilians don't get it.

34:24.563 --> 34:28.022
Or they get it,
but they just can't handle it.

34:29.775 --> 34:33.690
Okay, when I get back,
I'm gonna ask out Kathy.

34:34.281 --> 34:36.273
Okay. If you want to get your ass beat.

34:54.717 --> 34:56.208
My friend!

34:56.303 --> 34:57.293
Welcome.

34:58.555 --> 34:59.966
We have better inside.

35:00.807 --> 35:02.514
You come inside, we drink tea,

35:02.601 --> 35:04.342
and I show.

36:46.162 --> 36:49.451
We are not brothers.

37:11.813 --> 37:13.349
<i>This is the Western Union</i>

37:13.440 --> 37:16.274
<i>at South Las Vegas Boulevard?</i>

37:16.609 --> 37:19.568
I'm calling to check the status
of money sent.

37:19.654 --> 37:21.816
My tracking number is

37:21.906 --> 37:26.992
seven-four-nine-one-
eight-three-seven-zero-five.

37:31.166 --> 37:34.250
Good. Thank you. Have a good day.

37:48.057 --> 37:49.264
What are you doing here?

37:49.976 --> 37:51.217
I missed you.

37:52.270 --> 37:53.681
So, you flew back?

37:54.898 --> 37:56.560
I'm rotated out for the month.

37:57.567 --> 37:58.808
Oh.

38:01.946 --> 38:05.405
I drew a picture of happiness
for you on the plane.

38:14.918 --> 38:16.329
Who did that to you?

38:20.215 --> 38:21.751
You can't tell me.

38:24.677 --> 38:25.667
Can I come in?

38:27.514 --> 38:29.631
Yeah, of course you can come in.
I just...

38:30.391 --> 38:31.381
What?

38:33.353 --> 38:36.972
Ali, this isn't working. I need...

38:37.065 --> 38:39.057
- Don't break up with me.
- I never see you.

38:39.317 --> 38:41.604
You disappear. You reappear.
I can't ask you anything.

38:41.778 --> 38:43.064
- I know.
- I don't know who you are.

38:43.154 --> 38:44.861
- I don't know what you do.
- No, you know who I am.

38:44.989 --> 38:46.730
I don't want to live like this.
This is not what...

38:46.866 --> 38:48.232
You want someone totally predictable?

38:48.368 --> 38:50.701
- No. No, I want...
- I'm predictable.

38:51.579 --> 38:53.616
- I'll always come home to you.
- Ali...

38:53.790 --> 38:55.702
The second the plane lands,

38:56.584 --> 38:57.791
I'll come home to you.

39:00.088 --> 39:04.799
I hate not knowing where you are.
I hate that you might be in danger.

39:05.218 --> 39:08.006
Of course, you hate it.
It's good that you hate it.

39:08.179 --> 39:09.169
Why is it good?

39:09.264 --> 39:11.130
Because it means we're in love.

39:27.907 --> 39:28.897
What?

39:29.617 --> 39:32.860
"When love beckons to you, follow him,

39:33.246 --> 39:35.738
"though his ways are hard and steep."

39:37.584 --> 39:41.168
- Kahlil Gibran.
- Really?

39:42.297 --> 39:44.254
You're gonna quote poetry?

39:45.258 --> 39:48.217
Hi, honey. I'm home.

40:08.448 --> 40:10.815
Open your eyes.

40:20.043 --> 40:22.410
So, this is you?

40:22.587 --> 40:26.046
This is my first bed in America.
In Pennsylvania.

40:27.091 --> 40:30.755
And this is happiness because?

40:32.889 --> 40:35.506
Because maybe after a week,
I realized I never had to

40:35.600 --> 40:37.216
wake up in the middle
of the night again,

40:37.310 --> 40:39.472
and go to the bottom of the stairs.

40:40.063 --> 40:43.522
Why would you go
to the bottom of the stairs?

40:45.443 --> 40:48.356
That's the safest place in a house
when bombs are falling.

40:55.662 --> 40:56.778
I got a tip yesterday.

40:57.163 --> 40:58.904
- Pretty hot tip.
- Yeah?

40:59.207 --> 41:01.620
<i>The New York Times</i>
is gonna publish a story on you.

41:02.502 --> 41:04.038
I think I'd have heard about that.

41:05.672 --> 41:09.291
Basic thrust is that the security
of the country may be compromised

41:09.384 --> 41:12.297
because the Head of Counterterrorism
in New York

41:12.387 --> 41:15.095
was the subject
of intense internal scrutiny,

41:15.181 --> 41:18.515
following the loss of a briefcase
containing classified documents.

41:18.935 --> 41:22.224
- Where'd they get that from?
- I have no idea.

41:22.772 --> 41:25.059
So, kill it.

41:25.149 --> 41:27.106
I can kill it. I...

41:27.193 --> 41:30.607
You don't think I know the editor?
You think I haven't bought him dinner?

41:30.697 --> 41:31.938
You need to resign.

41:36.035 --> 41:37.947
No! No. I'm... Look...

41:38.037 --> 41:41.280
John. John, John, John.
I don't want to fire you.

41:41.582 --> 41:42.572
Good.

41:42.750 --> 41:44.332
So, you need to resign.

41:50.425 --> 41:54.135
I've been here 25 years.

41:54.971 --> 41:56.837
You need to resign today.

42:08.943 --> 42:12.277
Oh, no! We lost your hat.

42:14.782 --> 42:15.772
Thanks.

42:19.746 --> 42:20.827
How old?

42:21.205 --> 42:24.243
She'll be three. We just moved here.

42:24.333 --> 42:25.949
She's never seen the sea before.

42:27.295 --> 42:28.581
You want to get up?

42:29.297 --> 42:31.289
I'm gonna take her in.

42:34.844 --> 42:37.006
Oh, yeah. That's right!

42:38.222 --> 42:40.965
It's the sea. Yeah.

42:45.438 --> 42:47.350
I normally
don't attend the weekly

42:47.440 --> 42:49.978
counterterrorism meeting as a rule,

42:50.234 --> 42:52.100
but I wanted to be here today,
to underscore

42:52.195 --> 42:53.811
that from the CIA's perspective,

42:53.905 --> 42:58.400
there is nothing more urgent
than containing al-Qaeda.

42:58.493 --> 42:59.529
Thank you, George.

43:00.620 --> 43:04.330
I told your colleague the other day,
I don't deal in generalities.

43:04.499 --> 43:05.615
I need specifics.

43:05.875 --> 43:07.992
And specifics you shall have, good lady.

43:08.127 --> 43:10.619
The NSA's been hearing
a lot of chatter from

43:10.713 --> 43:12.921
various terrorist cells.
Correct, Michael?

43:13.216 --> 43:14.252
Roger that.

43:14.634 --> 43:17.968
We're concerned
about a potential attack on

43:18.054 --> 43:19.761
Jordan, Saudi Arabia, Israel...

43:19.847 --> 43:22.681
The word "potential"
is inherently unspecific.

43:22.767 --> 43:25.931
And Genoa, Italy,
for this year's G8 summit.

43:26.312 --> 43:28.679
Hey, George?
Listen, I gotta tell you something.

43:28.815 --> 43:30.772
I gotta tell all of you guys something.

43:31.192 --> 43:34.401
I'm gone. I'm out.

43:34.695 --> 43:35.685
I heard.

43:35.905 --> 43:39.364
So, this is my last meeting.
It's my last one of these.

43:40.076 --> 43:43.820
So, I just want to say
straight up to the Agency guys, okay?

43:44.956 --> 43:46.822
Maybe your people
won't talk to my people

43:46.916 --> 43:49.033
because somebody's got a hard-on for me.

43:49.127 --> 43:52.916
But I'm out of here.
It's not about me anymore.

43:53.005 --> 43:56.544
My people, my guys,
are trying to keep Americans safe.

43:57.844 --> 43:59.130
Forget the fucking Genoese
for a second...

43:59.220 --> 44:02.384
Maybe let Mr. Tenet finish, Mr...

44:04.350 --> 44:07.843
Mr. O'Neill
makes an excellent point.

44:07.937 --> 44:10.395
There are terrorists here.

44:10.523 --> 44:12.731
I explained to you
about the terrorist cells

44:12.817 --> 44:15.480
- and the transnational nature of...
- Who is here?

44:16.404 --> 44:19.988
Is there someone in the United States
that is a clear and present danger,

44:20.074 --> 44:22.157
that I need to be
worrying about right now,

44:22.285 --> 44:25.198
or are you talking about swatting flies?

44:25.288 --> 44:29.874
Because the President has told me
he has no interest in swatting flies.

44:31.711 --> 44:33.998
John's right.
We have had repeated trouble

44:34.088 --> 44:37.923
with the sharing of information
between Alec Station and I-49.

44:38.009 --> 44:41.377
Are you, George, aware of
any information that hasn't been shared?

44:44.891 --> 44:46.974
The President is correct.

44:47.059 --> 44:50.223
We need to have
a comprehensive strategy, which is why

44:50.313 --> 44:52.771
I'm meeting with him on Tuesday
when he gets back from Texas.

44:53.983 --> 44:57.067
Okay. Let's move on.

45:16.297 --> 45:19.631
This is the ladies' room.

45:19.800 --> 45:22.884
Or did you think you could have me, too?

45:27.475 --> 45:29.888
Don't you think
the world would be a better place

45:29.977 --> 45:32.435
if two people
could have an honest conversation

45:32.521 --> 45:34.729
about what's really going on?

45:42.073 --> 45:43.689
I think the world
would be a better place

45:43.783 --> 45:47.197
if old men
didn't hang around the ladies' room.

46:35.251 --> 46:36.537
George Tenet, please.

46:37.878 --> 46:38.959
Thank you.

46:43.467 --> 46:45.254
- Yes.
- George?

46:46.679 --> 46:49.763
<i>We must speak.</i>

